#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="pli-tv-bu-vb-np18"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:0.1"
msgid "Theravāda Vinaya"
msgstr "Theravāda Collection on Monastic Law"

#. HTML: </p><p class="division">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:0.2"
msgid "Mahāvibhaṅga"
msgstr "Monks’ rules and their analysis"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:0.3"
msgid "Nissaggiyakaṇḍa"
msgstr "The chapter on relinquishment"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:0.4"
msgid "Kosiyavagga"
msgstr "Monks’ Relinquishment"

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:0.5"
msgid "18. Rūpiyasikkhāpada"
msgstr "18. The training rule on money"

#. HTML: </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc1, pts-vp-pli3.237, pts-cs-bu-np18.1, pts-vp-en2.99, ms1V_2203
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.1"
msgid "Tena samayena buddho bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Rājagaha in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrel sanctuary."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā upanando sakyaputto aññatarassa kulassa kulūpako hoti niccabhattiko."
msgstr "At that time Venerable Upananda was associating with a family from which he received a regular meal."

#. VAR: paṭiviso → paṭiviṃso (bj)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.3"
msgid "Yaṃ tasmiṃ kule uppajjati khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā tato āyasmato upanandassa sakyaputtassa paṭiviso ṭhapiyyati."
msgstr "Whenever that family obtained food, they put aside a portion for Upananda."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.4"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena sāyaṃ tasmiṃ kule maṃsaṃ uppannaṃ hoti."
msgstr "And that’s what they did when one evening they obtained some meat."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.5"
msgid "Tato āyasmato upanandassa sakyaputtassa paṭiviso ṭhapito hoti."
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.6"
msgid "Tassa kulassa dārako rattiyā paccūsasamayaṃ paccuṭṭhāya rodati—"
msgstr "The following morning one of their children got up and cried,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.7"
msgid "“maṃsaṃ me dethā”ti."
msgstr "“Give me meat!”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.8"
msgid "Atha kho so puriso pajāpatiṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "The man said to his wife,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.9"
msgid "“ayyassa paṭivisaṃ dārakassa dehi."
msgstr "“Give the Venerable’s portion to the child."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.10"
msgid "Aññaṃ cetāpetvā ayyassa dassāmā”ti."
msgstr "We’ll buy something else for the Venerable.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2, ms1V_2204
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.11"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā upanando sakyaputto pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaraṃ ādāya yena taṃ kulaṃ tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "On the same morning Upananda robed up, took his bowl and robe, and went to that family,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.12"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi."
msgstr "where he sat down on the prepared seat."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.13"
msgid "Atha kho so puriso yenāyasmā upanando sakyaputto tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "The man of the house approached Upananda,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.14"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ upanandaṃ sakyaputtaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi."
msgstr "bowed down to him, sat down to one side,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.15"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so puriso āyasmantaṃ upanandaṃ sakyaputtaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "and said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.16"
msgid "“hiyyo kho, bhante, sāyaṃ maṃsaṃ uppannaṃ ahosi."
msgstr "“Yesterday evening, Venerable, we obtained some meat,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.17"
msgid "Tato ayyassa paṭiviso ṭhapito."
msgstr "and we put aside a portion for you."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.18"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhante, dārako rattiyā paccūsasamayaṃ paccuṭṭhāya rodati—"
msgstr "But then in the morning our child got up and cried,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.19"
msgid "‘maṃsaṃ me dethā’ti."
msgstr "‘Give me meat!’,"

#. REF: pts-vp-en2.100
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.20"
msgid "Ayyassa paṭiviso dārakassa dinno."
msgstr "and we gave your portion to the child."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.21"
msgid "Kahāpaṇena, bhante, kiṃ āhariyyatū”ti?"
msgstr "What can we get you for the sum of a _kahāpaṇa_?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.22"
msgid "“Pariccatto me, āvuso, kahāpaṇo”ti?"
msgstr "“Are you giving up a _kahāpaṇa_ coin for me?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.23"
msgid "“Āma, bhante, pariccatto”ti."
msgstr "“Yes, Venerable.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.24"
msgid "“Taññeva me, āvuso, kahāpaṇaṃ dehī”ti."
msgstr "“Then just give me that _kahāpaṇa_.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3, ms1V_2205
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.25"
msgid "Atha kho so puriso āyasmato upanandassa sakyaputtassa kahāpaṇaṃ datvā ujjhāyati khiyyati vipāceti—"
msgstr "After giving a _kahāpaṇa_ to Upananda, that man grumbled and complained,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.26"
msgid "“Yatheva mayaṃ rūpiyaṃ paṭiggaṇhāma evamevime samaṇā sakyaputtiyā rūpiyaṃ paṭiggaṇhantī”ti."
msgstr "“Just as we accept money, so do the Sakyan ascetics.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-en2.101
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.27"
msgid "Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tassa purisassa ujjhāyantassa khiyyantassa vipācentassa."
msgstr "The monks heard the complaints of that man,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.28"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "and the monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.29"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized him,”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.30"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma āyasmā upanando sakyaputto rūpiyaṃ paṭiggahessatī”ti."
msgstr "“How can Venerable Upananda receive money?"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4, ms1V_2206
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.31"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū āyasmantaṃ upanandaṃ sakyaputtaṃ anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "After criticizing him in many ways, they told the Master. …"

#. VAR: paṭiggahesī”ti → paṭiggaṇhāsīti (s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.32"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, upananda, rūpiyaṃ paṭiggahesī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, Upananda, that you did this?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.33"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.34"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked him, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.35"
msgid "kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, rūpiyaṃ paṭiggahessasi."
msgstr "Foolish man, how can you receive money?"

#. REF: pts-vp-en2.102
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.36"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.37"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.37a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="rule"> 
#. REF: sc5, ms1V_2207
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.38"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu jātarūparajataṃ uggaṇheyya vā uggaṇhāpeyya vā upanikkhittaṃ vā sādiyeyya, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "‘If a monk takes, gets someone else to take, or consents to gold and silver being deposited for him, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.38a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc6, ms1V_2208, pts-vp-pli3.238
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.39"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr "A:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.40"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "whoever …"

#. HTML: </span><span class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.41"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "Monk:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.42"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr "… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.43"
msgid "ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc7, ms1V_2209
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.44"
msgid "Jātarūpaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Gold:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.45"
msgid "satthuvaṇṇo vuccati."
msgstr "the color of the Teacher is what is meant."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc8, ms1V_2210
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.46"
msgid "Rajataṃ nāma"
msgstr "Silver:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.47"
msgid "kahāpaṇo lohamāsako dārumāsako jatumāsako ye vohāraṃ gacchanti."
msgstr "a _kahāpaṇa_ coin, a copper _māsaka_ coin, a wooden _māsaka_ coin, a resin _māsaka_ coin; whatever is used in commerce."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc9, pts-vp-en2.103, ms1V_2211
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.48"
msgid "Uggaṇheyyāti"
msgstr "Takes:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
#. VAR: nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ → nissaggiyaṃ hoti (s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.49"
msgid "sayaṃ gaṇhāti nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "if he takes it himself, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc10, ms1V_2212
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.50"
msgid "Uggaṇhāpeyyāti"
msgstr "Gets someone else to take:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
#. VAR: nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ → nissaggiyaṃ hoti (s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.51"
msgid "aññaṃ gāhāpeti nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "if he gets another to take it, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc11, ms1V_2213
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.52"
msgid "Upanikkhittaṃ vā sādiyeyyāti"
msgstr "Consents to […] being deposited for him:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.53"
msgid "idaṃ ayyassa hotūti upanikkhittaṃ sādiyati, nissaggiyaṃ hoti."
msgstr "if someone says, “Let this be for you,” and he consents to it being deposited for him, it becomes subject to relinquishment."

#. HTML: </span></p><hr><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.54"
msgid "Saṃghamajjhe nissajjitabbaṃ."
msgstr "It should be relinquished in the midst of the Order."

#. HTML: <span class="kamma">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.55"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, nissajjitabbaṃ—"
msgstr "“And, monks, it should be relinquished in this way."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.56"
msgid "tena bhikkhunā saṃghaṃ upasaṅkamitvā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā vuḍḍhānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ pāde vanditvā ukkuṭikaṃ nisīditvā añjaliṃ paggahetvā evamassa vacanīyo—"
msgstr "After approaching the Order, that monk should put his upper robe over one shoulder and pay respect at the feet of the senior monks. He should then squat on his heels, put the palms of his hands together, and say,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.57"
msgid "“ahaṃ, bhante, rūpiyaṃ paṭiggahesiṃ."
msgstr "‘Venerables, I have received money."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.58"
msgid "Idaṃ me nissaggiyaṃ."
msgstr "It is to be relinquished."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.59"
msgid "Imāhaṃ saṃghassa nissajjāmī”ti."
msgstr "I relinquish it to the Order.’"

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.60"
msgid "Nissajjitvā āpatti desetabbā."
msgstr "”After relinquishing it, he is to confess the offense."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.61"
msgid "Byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena āpatti paṭiggahetabbā."
msgstr "The confession should be received by a competent and capable monk."

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.62"
msgid "Sace tattha āgacchati ārāmiko vā upāsako vā so vattabbo—"
msgstr "If a monastery worker or a lay follower is available, you should tell him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.63"
msgid "“āvuso, imaṃ jānāhī”ti."
msgstr "“Look into this.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.64"
msgid "Sace so bhaṇati—"
msgstr "If he says,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.65"
msgid "“iminā kiṃ āhariyyatū”ti,"
msgstr "“What can I get you with this?”,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.66"
msgid "na vattabbo—"
msgstr "you should not say,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.67"
msgid "“imaṃ vā imaṃ vā āharā”ti."
msgstr "“Get this or that;”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.68"
msgid "Kappiyaṃ ācikkhitabbaṃ—"
msgstr "you should point out what is allowable:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.69"
msgid "sappi vā telaṃ vā madhu vā phāṇitaṃ vā."
msgstr "ghee, oil, honey, or sugar."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.70"
msgid "Sace so tena parivattetvā kappiyaṃ āharati rūpiyappaṭiggāhakaṃ ṭhapetvā sabbeheva paribhuñjitabbaṃ."
msgstr "If he makes a purchase and brings back what is allowable, everyone may enjoy it except the one who received the money."

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.71"
msgid "Evañcetaṃ labhetha, iccetaṃ kusalaṃ;"
msgstr "If this is what happens, that is good."

#. REF: pts-vp-en2.104
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.72"
msgid "no ce labhetha, so vattabbo—"
msgstr "If not, you should tell him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.73"
msgid "“āvuso, imaṃ chaḍḍehī”ti."
msgstr "“Discard this.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.74"
msgid "Sace so chaḍḍeti, iccetaṃ kusalaṃ;"
msgstr "If he discards it, that is good."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.75"
msgid "no ce chaḍḍeti, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu rūpiyachaḍḍako sammannitabbo—"
msgstr "If he does not, a monk who has five qualities should be appointed as the money-discarder:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.76"
msgid "yo na chandāgatiṃ gaccheyya, na dosāgatiṃ gaccheyya, na mohāgatiṃ gaccheyya, na bhayāgatiṃ gaccheyya, chaḍḍitāchaḍḍitañca jāneyya."
msgstr "one who is not swayed by desire, ill will, confusion, or fear, and who understands the meaning of discarded and not discarded."

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.77"
msgid "“Evañca pana, bhikkhave, sammannitabbo."
msgstr "“And, monks, this is how he should be appointed."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.78"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ bhikkhu yācitabbo."
msgstr "First the monk should be asked"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.79"
msgid "Yācitvā byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṃgho ñāpetabbo—"
msgstr "and then a competent and capable monk should inform the Order:"

#. HTML: </p><div class="kamma"><p>
#. REF: sc12, ms1V_2214
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.80"
msgid "‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṃgho."
msgstr "‘Venerables, let the Order listen to me."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.81"
msgid "Yadi saṃghassa pattakallaṃ, saṃgho itthannāmaṃ bhikkhuṃ rūpiyachaḍḍakaṃ sammanneyya."
msgstr "If it seems appropriate to the Order, it should appoint monk so-and-so as the money-discarder."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.82"
msgid "Esā ñatti."
msgstr "This is the motion."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc13, ms1V_2215
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.83"
msgid "Suṇātu me, bhante, saṃgho."
msgstr "Venerables, let the Order listen to me."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.84"
msgid "Saṃgho itthannāmaṃ bhikkhuṃ rūpiyachaḍḍakaṃ sammannati."
msgstr "The Order appoints monk so-and-so as the money-discarder."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.85"
msgid "Yassāyasmato khamati itthannāmassa bhikkhuno rūpiyachaḍḍakassa sammuti, so tuṇhassa;"
msgstr "Any monk who agrees to appointing monk so-and-so as the money-discarder should remain silent."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.86"
msgid "yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya."
msgstr "Any monk who does not agree should speak up."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc14, ms1V_2216
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.87"
msgid "Sammato saṃghena itthannāmo bhikkhu rūpiyachaḍḍako."
msgstr "The Order has appointed monk so-and-so as the money-discarder."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.88"
msgid "Khamati saṃghassa, tasmā tuṇhī,"
msgstr "The Order approves and is therefore silent."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.89"
msgid "evametaṃ dhārayāmī’”ti."
msgstr "I will remember it thus.’”"

#. HTML: </p></div><p><span class="rule"> 
#. REF: sc15, ms1V_2217
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.90"
msgid "Tena sammatena bhikkhunā animittaṃ katvā pātetabbaṃ."
msgstr "The appointed monk should drop it without taking note of the location."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.91"
msgid "Sace nimittaṃ katvā pāteti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he takes note of where he drops it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.91a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc16, pts-vp-pli3.239, pts-vp-en2.105, ms1V_2218
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.92"
msgid "Rūpiye rūpiyasaññī rūpiyaṃ paṭiggaṇhāti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If it is money, and he perceives it as money, and he receives it, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.93"
msgid "Rūpiye vematiko rūpiyaṃ paṭiggaṇhāti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If it is money, but he is unsure if it is, and he receives it, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.94"
msgid "Rūpiye arūpiyasaññī rūpiyaṃ paṭiggaṇhāti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If it is money, but he does not perceive it as money, and he receives it, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc17, ms1V_2219
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.95"
msgid "Arūpiye rūpiyasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If it is not money, but he perceives it as money, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.96"
msgid "Arūpiye vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If it is not money, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.97"
msgid "Arūpiye arūpiyasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr "If it is not money, and he does not perceive it as money, there is no offense."

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.97a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc18, ms1V_2220
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.98"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.99"
msgid "ajjhārāme vā ajjhāvasathe vā uggahetvā vā uggahāpetvā vā nikkhipati—"
msgstr "if, within a monastery or a house, he takes it or gets someone to take it, and then puts it aside with the thought,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.100"
msgid "yassa bhavissati so harissatīti,"
msgstr "“Whoever this belongs to will fetch it;”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.101"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.102"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. HTML: </p><hr><p class="endsutta">
#. VAR: Rūpiyasikkhāpadaṃ → jāta­rūpa­sikkhā­pada (kaṅkhāvitaraṇī)
#. REF: sc19, ms1V_2221,
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np18:1.103"
msgid "Rūpiyasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ aṭṭhamaṃ."
msgstr "The eighth rule, the training rule on money, is finished."
